      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#0096D6] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
          Zakat FAQs
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-600 text-base mb-8" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
          <p>Please note that for any specific queries, it is advisable to contact your local imam.</p>
          <p>You can use our <a href="/zakat-calculator" class="text-[#0096D6] font-bold underline underline-offset-2">Zakat Calculator</a> to calculate how much you need to give.</p>
          <p>Here's a list of <strong class="text-gray-800">Frequently Asked Questions</strong> that you can use for further guidance:</p>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Accordion -->
        <div class="divide-y divide-gray-200 border-t border-gray-200" id="zakat-faq-list">
          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">What is Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Zakat is one of the Five Pillars of Islam. It is a mandatory act of charity requiring eligible Muslims to give 2.5% of their qualifying wealth annually to those in need. Unlike voluntary charity (Sadaqah), Zakat is an obligation prescribed in the Quran and is a means of purifying one's wealth and helping the most vulnerable.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">How much is Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Zakat is 2.5% of your total qualifying wealth that has been held for one full lunar year (Hawl). Qualifying wealth includes cash, savings, gold, silver, investments, and business assets — minus any outstanding debts. For example, if your net zakatable assets total $20,000, your Zakat would be $500.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">What is Nisab?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Nisab is the minimum amount of wealth a person must own before Zakat becomes obligatory. It is calculated using the value of either 87.48 grams of gold or 612.36 grams of silver. Most scholars recommend using the silver standard as it has a lower threshold, meaning more people are eligible to pay and more people in need can benefit.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">What is Hawl, and should it be based on lunar or solar years?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Hawl refers to the completion of one full year of wealth ownership above the nisab threshold. Traditionally, Hawl is based on the lunar calendar (approximately 354 days). However, many scholars accept the solar calendar (365 days) as well, especially for ease of calculation. If using the solar year, some scholars recommend paying slightly more (2.578%) to account for the extra days.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Who is eligible to receive Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              The Quran (Surah At-Tawbah 9:60) defines eight categories of Zakat recipients: (1) Al-Fuqara — the poor, (2) Al-Masakin — the needy, (3) Amil Zakah — administrators of Zakat, (4) Mu'allafat al-Quloob — those whose hearts are to be reconciled, (5) Ar-Riqab — those in bondage, (6) Al-Gharimin — those in debt, (7) Fi Sabilillah — in the cause of Allah, and (8) Ibn as-Sabil — the stranded traveler.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Do non-Muslims have to pay Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              No. Zakat is a religious obligation specific to Muslims. It is one of the Five Pillars of Islam. However, non-Muslims are welcome to make voluntary charitable donations (Sadaqah) through our platform to support humanitarian causes.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">What is Zakat al-Mal?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Zakat al-Mal (Zakat on wealth) is the standard form of Zakat — 2.5% of accumulated wealth above the nisab held for one year. This is distinct from Zakat al-Fitr (Fitrana), which is a fixed amount given before Eid al-Fitr prayers at the end of Ramadan. Both are obligations, but they serve different purposes.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I give a lot to charity throughout the year. Do I still have to pay Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Yes. Voluntary charity (Sadaqah) and Zakat are separate obligations. Sadaqah does not replace or reduce your Zakat obligation. However, if you explicitly made a donation with the intention (niyyah) of it being Zakat at the time of giving, that amount can count toward your Zakat. Intention matters in Islam.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Miscellaneous Questions -->
        <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#0096D6] mt-12 mb-6" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
          Common Scenarios
        </h3>
        <div class="divide-y divide-gray-200 border-t border-gray-200" id="zakat-faq-misc">
          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I owe several years of Zakat. How do I pay?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              You should calculate Zakat for each missed year based on the wealth you held at that time. Start from the earliest year you missed and work forward. If exact figures are unavailable, estimate to the best of your ability. It's better to pay slightly more to ensure the obligation is fulfilled. You can pay all accumulated Zakat at once.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Is Zakat due on a child's wealth if it exceeds the nisab?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              This is a matter of scholarly difference. The majority of scholars (including the Shafi'i, Maliki, and Hanbali schools) hold that Zakat is due on a child's wealth if it meets the nisab and has been held for one year — the guardian should pay it on their behalf. The Hanafi school holds that Zakat is not obligatory until the child reaches puberty. Consult your local scholar for guidance specific to your situation.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">How do I calculate Zakat on gold, silver, and mixed jewelry?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              For pure gold or silver, calculate the current market value and pay 2.5%. For mixed jewelry containing gold, silver, and precious stones, only the gold and silver portions are zakatable — precious stones are generally exempt. Have a jeweler assess the weight of gold and silver separately, then calculate 2.5% of each based on current market prices.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Can I pay Zakat in advance before my Hawl is complete?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Yes, the majority of scholars permit paying Zakat in advance (before the Hawl completes), especially during blessed times like Ramadan. If you pay early and your wealth drops below the nisab before your Hawl completes, what you paid would count as voluntary charity (Sadaqah) rather than Zakat.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Is Zakat due on rental property or a home I plan to sell?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              A property you live in is not subject to Zakat. A rental property itself is also not zakatable, but the rental income you receive and save is part of your zakatable wealth. However, if you purchased a property with the intention of selling it for profit (business inventory), then its market value is zakatable. If you later decide to sell a personal home, Zakat becomes due from the point you made that intention.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Should I include savings for Hajj when calculating Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Yes. Money saved for Hajj is still part of your total wealth and is included in your Zakat calculation. Even though it is earmarked for a specific purpose, it remains in your possession and contributes to your overall zakatable assets until it is spent.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I paid Zakat last year. This year my wealth has increased. What value do I take the 2.5% from?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              You calculate 2.5% on your <strong>total current zakatable wealth</strong> at the time your Hawl completes — not just the increase. For example, if you paid Zakat on $4,000 last year and now have $10,000 in total zakatable wealth, you pay 2.5% of the full $10,000 (which is $250). Previous Zakat payments do not reduce your current obligation because Zakat is assessed on the wealth you hold today, not the growth from last year.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Business, Property and Debt -->
        <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#0096D6] mt-12 mb-6" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
          Business, Property &amp; Debt
        </h3>
        <div class="divide-y divide-gray-200 border-t border-gray-200" id="zakat-faq-business">
          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I lent money to a friend who says they can return it. Do I include this in my Zakat calculation?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Yes. If you have a reasonable expectation that the money will be returned (the debtor acknowledges the debt and has the ability to pay), then that amount is considered part of your wealth. You should include it in your Zakat calculation. However, if there is doubt about whether the money will be recovered, some scholars say you can defer Zakat on that portion until you actually receive it — at which point you would pay Zakat for the years it was owed.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I lent money years ago to someone poor and didn't expect repayment. They've now repaid me. Is this liable for Zakat?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              When you receive unexpected repayment of a loan you had written off, the money becomes part of your zakatable wealth from the moment you receive it. According to most scholars, you should pay Zakat on this amount for the current year. Some scholars hold that you should also pay Zakat retroactively for the years the debt was outstanding, while others say only for the current year since you had no access to it. The safer position is to pay for at least one full year upon receipt.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">My Zakat is due in Dhul-Qa'dah but I want to pay early in Ramadan. I also have a debt due after Ramadan. Can I deduct this debt?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              This is a nuanced scenario. If you choose to pay Zakat early in Ramadan (which is permissible), you should calculate based on your wealth at that time. Regarding the upcoming debt: debts that are due within the year can generally be deducted from your zakatable wealth. So yes, if you have a known debt due in Shawwal, you can subtract that amount before calculating your 2.5%. However, long-term debts (like a mortgage) are treated differently — only the current year's installments are typically deducted. Consult a scholar for your specific situation.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I bought a house to rent out 5 years ago but recently decided to sell it. How do I pay Zakat on this?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              When a property is held for rental income, the property itself is not subject to Zakat — only the rental income you save is zakatable. However, the moment you change your intention to selling the property for profit, it becomes classified as a trade asset. From that point forward, the market value of the property is included in your zakatable wealth. So if you decided to sell last year, you would calculate Zakat on its current market value from the date you formed that intention, provided one full Hawl has passed since then.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">I own a shop or business. How do I calculate Zakat on it?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              For a business, Zakat is calculated on the trade inventory (goods available for sale at current market value), plus any cash, receivables, and savings held by the business — minus any business debts due within the year. Fixed assets used in operations (equipment, premises, vehicles) are not subject to Zakat. For a clothing shop, for example, you would calculate the wholesale or market value of all unsold stock, add your business cash and receivables, subtract short-term liabilities, and pay 2.5% on the total.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Is Zakat due on stocks, mutual funds, and retirement accounts (401k/IRA)?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Yes, stocks and mutual funds are generally zakatable at their current market value. For actively traded stocks (bought for resale), Zakat is on the full market value. For long-term investments (held for dividends), many scholars say Zakat is only on the dividends received. Retirement accounts like 401(k) and IRA: if accessible (even with penalties), the majority view is that Zakat is due on the current value minus any early withdrawal penalties and taxes. Some scholars defer Zakat on locked accounts until the money becomes accessible. Use our <a href="/zakat-calculator" class="text-[#0096D6] underline font-semibold">Zakat Calculator</a> to help with these calculations.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Can I deduct my mortgage from my zakatable wealth?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              You cannot deduct the entire mortgage balance from your zakatable wealth. Scholars generally agree that only the payments due within the current year (typically 12 monthly payments) can be deducted. This is because a mortgage is a long-term liability and deducting the full amount would exempt most homeowners from Zakat entirely, which goes against the spirit of the obligation. So if your annual mortgage payments total $24,000, you deduct that from your total wealth before calculating 2.5%.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="zakat-faq-item">
            <button class="zakat-faq-toggle w-full flex items-center gap-4 py-5 text-left cursor-pointer group">
              <svg class="zakat-faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 group-hover:text-[#0096D6] transition flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
              <span class="font-bold text-gray-700 text-base md:text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">Is Zakat due on cryptocurrency (Bitcoin, Ethereum, etc.)?</span>
            </button>
            <div class="zakat-faq-body hidden pb-5 pl-9 text-gray-600 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              Yes. Contemporary scholars generally agree that cryptocurrency is a form of digital wealth and is subject to Zakat. If held for trading purposes, Zakat is due on the full market value. If held as a long-term investment, it is still considered zakatable wealth similar to cash savings. Calculate the market value of your crypto holdings on your Zakat due date and include it in your total zakatable assets. The 2.5% rate applies as with any other form of wealth.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Where Your Zakat Goes — Category Cards (only if items exist) -->
    {categoryCards.length > 0 && (
      <section class="py-14 md:py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
          <div class="text-center mb-10">
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;" set:html={pageContent.howDonationHelps.heading.replace(/\*(.*?)\*/g, '<span class="text-[#e1861d]">$1</span>')} />
            {pageContent.howDonationHelps.subheading && (
              <p class="text-gray-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
                {pageContent.howDonationHelps.subheading}
              </p>
            )}
          </div>

          <div class={`grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-${Math.min(categoryCards.length, 4)} gap-4 md:gap-6`}>
            {categoryCards.map((card: { amount: string; label: string }, index: number) => (
              <div class={`bg-gradient-to-br ${cardGradients[index % cardGradients.length]} rounded-xl p-5 text-white text-center`}>
                <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-white/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3">
                  <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <Fragment set:html={cardIcons[index % cardIcons.length]} />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-sm md:text-base mb-1" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">{card.amount}</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-300 hidden md:block">{card.label}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <!-- Hadith / Mid CTA Banner (only if heading exists) -->
    {pageContent.midCta.heading && savedPC.midCta?.heading && (
      <section class="py-10 md:py-12 bg-[#255764]">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
          <p class="text-white/80 text-lg md:text-xl italic mb-3" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
            {pageContent.midCta.heading}
          </p>
          {pageContent.midCta.subtext && (
            <p class="text-[#e1861d] font-bold text-sm">{pageContent.midCta.subtext}</p>
          )}
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <!-- Calculator Callout Strip -->
    <section class="py-10 md:py-12 bg-[#0096D6]">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-5">
          <div class="text-white text-center md:text-left">
            <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-1" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
              Not Sure How Much Zakat You Owe?
            </h3>
            <p class="text-blue-100 text-sm md:text-base">
              Use our free Zakat calculator to find your exact obligation in minutes.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a href="/zakat-calculator" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-white text-[#0096D6] font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-100 transition shadow-lg whitespace-nowrap" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path d="M6 2a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2h8a2 2 0 002-2V4a2 2 0 00-2-2H6zm0 2h8v2H6V4zm0 4h2v2H6V8zm0 3h2v2H6v-2zm0 3h2v2H6v-2zm3-6h2v2H9V8zm0 3h2v2H9v-2zm0 3h2v2H9v-2zm3-6h2v2h-2V8zm0 3h2v5h-2v-5z"></path></svg>
            Calculate My Zakat
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Links -->
    {quickLinks.length > 0 && (
      <section class="py-14 md:py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-8 text-center" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
            Learn More About Zakat
          </h2>

          <div class={`grid md:grid-cols-${Math.min(quickLinks.length, 3)} gap-5`}>
            {quickLinks.map((link: { title: string; description: string; url: string; color: string }) => (
              <a href={link.url} class="group bg-stone-50 rounded-xl p-5 hover:shadow-lg transition border border-gray-100">
                <div class="w-11 h-11 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-3 group-hover:scale-110 transition" style={`background-color: ${link.color}`}>
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-white" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12.586 4.586a2 2 0 112.828 2.828l-3 3a2 2 0 01-2.828 0 1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414 4 4 0 005.656 0l3-3a4 4 0 00-5.656-5.656l-1.5 1.5a1 1 0 101.414 1.414l1.5-1.5zm-5 5a2 2 0 012.828 0 1 1 0 101.414-1.414 4 4 0 00-5.656 0l-3 3a4 4 0 105.656 5.656l1.5-1.5a1 1 0 10-1.414-1.414l-1.5 1.5a2 2 0 11-2.828-2.828l3-3z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-1" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">{link.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{link.description}</p>
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <!-- Final CTA -->
    {savedPC.finalCta?.heading && (
      <section class="py-14 md:py-16 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#255764] to-[#1a3d47] text-white">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
            {pageContent.finalCta.heading}
          </h2>
          {pageContent.finalCta.subtext && (
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto" style="font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;">
              {pageContent.finalCta.subtext}
            </p>
          )}
          <button id="final-cta-btn" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#e1861d] hover:bg-[#c97418] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-xl transition-all hover:scale-105 cursor-pointer shadow-lg text-lg" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
            {pageContent.finalCta.primaryButtonText || 'Pay Your Zakat Now'}
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"></path></svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </section>
    )}
  </main>

  <!-- Mobile Sticky CTA Bar -->
  <div id="zakat-sticky-bar" class="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 lg:hidden translate-y-full transition-transform duration-300">
    <div class="bg-white border-t border-gray-200 shadow-[0_-4px_20px_rgba(0,0,0,0.1)] px-4 py-3">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-bold text-gray-800">{stickyBar.title}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">{stickyBar.subtitle}</p>
        </div>
        <button id="zakat-sticky-btn" class="bg-[#DC1A34] hover:bg-[#b8162c] text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-xl text-sm flex items-center gap-2 transition-all cursor-pointer whitespace-nowrap" style="font-family: 'Signika', sans-serif;">
          <span id="sticky-btn-text">{stickyBar.buttonText}</span>
          <span id="sticky-btn-amount" class="hidden bg-white/20 rounded-lg px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-bold"></span>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const donationBox = document.querySelector('[data-zakat-donate]');

    // Scroll to donation box
    function scrollToDonationBox() {
      if (donationBox) {
        const rect = donationBox.getBoundingClientRect();
        const scrollTarget = window.pageYOffset + rect.top - 20;
        window.scrollTo({ top: Math.max(0, scrollTarget), behavior: 'smooth' });
      }
    }

    // Hero button
    document.getElementById('hero-give-btn')?.addEventListener('click', scrollToDonationBox);
    // What is Zakat donate button
    document.getElementById('what-is-zakat-donate-btn')?.addEventListener('click', scrollToDonationBox);
    // Final CTA button
    document.getElementById('final-cta-btn')?.addEventListener('click', scrollToDonationBox);

    // Impact card donate buttons — add to cart and open checkout directly
    document.querySelectorAll('.zakat-impact-donate-btn').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const amount = parseInt((btn as HTMLElement).dataset.amount || '0', 10);
        if (amount > 0 && typeof (window as any).addToCart === 'function') {
          (window as any).addToCart({
            id: 'zakat-' + amount,
            name: 'Zakat',
            label: 'Zakat',
            amount: amount,
            quantity: 1,
            type: 'single',
            recurringInterval: null,
            image: document.querySelector('[data-zakat-donate] img')?.getAttribute('src') || '',
            campaign: 'zakat'
          });
        }
      });
    });

    // Fetch live metal prices for Nisab display
    (async () => {
      try {
        const res = await fetch('/api/metal-prices');
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error('fetch failed');
        const data = await res.json();
        if (!data.success) throw new Error('no data');
        const goldNisab = data.gold * 87.48;
        const silverNisab = data.silver * 612.36;
        const fmt = (v: number) => '$' + v.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0 });
        const goldEl = document.getElementById('nisab-gold-val');
        const silverEl = document.getElementById('nisab-silver-val');
        const dateEl = document.getElementById('nisab-date-label');
        if (goldEl) goldEl.textContent = '~' + fmt(goldNisab);
        if (silverEl) silverEl.textContent = '~' + fmt(silverNisab);
        if (dateEl) {
          const d = data.timestamp ? new Date(data.timestamp) : new Date();
          dateEl.textContent = 'Nisab as of ' + d.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'short', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' });
        }
      } catch (e) {
        // Fallback values
        const goldEl = document.getElementById('nisab-gold-val');
        const silverEl = document.getElementById('nisab-silver-val');
        if (goldEl) goldEl.textContent = '~$19,324';
        if (silverEl) silverEl.textContent = '~$2,180';
      }
    })();

    // FAQ accordion toggle
    document.querySelectorAll('.zakat-faq-toggle').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const body = btn.nextElementSibling as HTMLElement;
        const icon = btn.querySelector('.zakat-faq-icon') as SVGElement;
        const isOpen = !body.classList.contains('hidden');
        // Close all
        document.querySelectorAll('.zakat-faq-body').forEach(b => b.classList.add('hidden'));
        document.querySelectorAll('.zakat-faq-icon').forEach(i => {
          (i as SVGElement).style.transform = '';
          i.classList.remove('text-[#0096D6]');
          i.classList.add('text-gray-400');
        });
        // Open this one if it was closed
        if (!isOpen) {
          body.classList.remove('hidden');
          if (icon) {
            icon.style.transform = 'rotate(45deg)';
            icon.classList.remove('text-gray-400');
            icon.classList.add('text-[#0096D6]');
          }
        }
      });
    });

    // "Give your Zakat today" link
    document.getElementById('give-zakat-today-link')?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      scrollToDonationBox();
    });

    // Add to cart and open checkout helper for impact cards
    window.addToCartAndCheckout = function(name: string, amount: number, campaign: string) {
      if (window.addToCart) {
        window.addToCart({
          id: campaign + '-' + amount,
          name: name,
          campaign: campaign,
          amount: amount,
          type: 'single',
          quantity: 1
        });
      }
    };

    // Impact carousel
    const carouselTrack = document.getElementById('zakat-carousel-track');
    const carouselDots = document.querySelectorAll('.zakat-carousel-dot');
    const totalSlides = carouselDots.length;
    let currentSlide = 0;

    function goToSlide(index: number) {
      currentSlide = ((index % totalSlides) + totalSlides) % totalSlides;
      if (carouselTrack) {
        carouselTrack.style.transform = `translateX(-${currentSlide * 100}%)`;
      }
      carouselDots.forEach((dot, i) => {
        dot.classList.toggle('bg-[#0096D6]', i === currentSlide);
        dot.classList.toggle('bg-[#0096D6]/30', i !== currentSlide);
      });
    }

    document.getElementById('zakat-carousel-prev')?.addEventListener('click', () => goToSlide(currentSlide - 1));
    document.getElementById('zakat-carousel-next')?.addEventListener('click', () => goToSlide(currentSlide + 1));
    carouselDots.forEach(dot => {
      dot.addEventListener('click', () => goToSlide(parseInt((dot as HTMLElement).dataset.slide || '0', 10)));
    });

    // Touch swipe support for carousel
    let touchStartX = 0;
    const carouselEl = document.getElementById('zakat-carousel');
    carouselEl?.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => { touchStartX = e.touches[0].clientX; }, { passive: true });
    carouselEl?.addEventListener('touchend', (e) => {
      const diff = touchStartX - e.changedTouches[0].clientX;
      if (Math.abs(diff) > 50) {
        goToSlide(diff > 0 ? currentSlide + 1 : currentSlide - 1);
      }
    }, { passive: true });

    // Mobile sticky bar — show when donation box is NOT visible, hide when it IS
    const stickyBar = document.getElementById('zakat-sticky-bar');
    const stickyBtn = document.getElementById('zakat-sticky-btn');

    stickyBtn?.addEventListener('click', scrollToDonationBox);

    // Update sticky button with selected amount
    const stickyBtnAmount = document.getElementById('sticky-btn-amount');
    document.addEventListener('cw:amount-change', (e) => {
      const amt = (e as CustomEvent).detail?.amount;
      if (stickyBtnAmount && amt > 0) {
        stickyBtnAmount.textContent = '$' + amt.toLocaleString();
        stickyBtnAmount.classList.remove('hidden');
      } else if (stickyBtnAmount) {
        stickyBtnAmount.classList.add('hidden');
      }
    });

    if (stickyBar && donationBox) {
      const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
        ([entry]) => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            stickyBar.classList.add('translate-y-full');
          } else {
            stickyBar.classList.remove('translate-y-full');
          }
        },
        { threshold: 0.1 }
      );
      observer.observe(donationBox);
    }
  });
</script>
